      "text": "It’s not actually a secret and it certainly shouldn’t be: documentation needs to include and be structured around its four different functions: tutorials, how-to guides, technical reference and explanation. Each of them requires a distinct mode of writing. People working with software need these four different kinds of documentation at different times, in different circumstances – so software usually needs them all, and they should all be integrated into your documentation."
